com.github.javaparser.ast.expr

Class Name

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.javaparser.ast.Node
      • com.github.javaparser.ast.expr.Name
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NodeWithAnnotations<Name>, NodeWithIdentifier<Name>, NodeWithRange<Node>, NodeWithTokenRange<Node>, Observable, Visitable, HasParentNode<Node>, Cloneable

    public final class Name
extends Node
implements NodeWithIdentifier<Name>, NodeWithAnnotations<Name>
    A name that may consist of multiple identifiers. In other words: it.may.contain.dots.

    The rightmost identifier is "identifier", The one to the left of it is "qualifier.identifier", etc.

    You can construct one from a String with the name(...) method.

    Author:
    Julio Vilmar Gesser
    See Also:
    SimpleName
